The paper discusses a model for sequential multi-task deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the issue of catastrophic interference in deep architectures, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The empirical results presented in the paper involve image recognition tasks, which are typically studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
